1502. To HIEROSLAUS LASKY.

Modus orandi Deum fo· a'2. <Basle.> LB. v. 1099. <0. October 1524.)

[The opening and concluding passages of the M odas orandi Deum, Basle, Froben, Oct. 1524 (α) : which has no formal preface. In a second Froben edition, March 1525 (β), and in the Basle Opera, 1540. v. 917 (γ), are some trifling variants. Being directed against Luther (Ep. 1559 fin.) the book was suitable for dedication to Lasky (Ep. 1242. 250), in response to his request made in May 1524 (1, pp. 31. 32). It was in the press on 13 Oct. (Ep. 1506. 2). Translations soon appeared, into French by Berquin (Ep. 925. 130) 3. a.. and into German, printed by Froben. 15253 also int-o Dutch 1616]
